name: Agata Maszkiewicz
bio: Costume designer | coffee addict | chocolate lover and excellent napper| Los Angeles|

social_posts.post_text: Happy Holidays. I hope you all having a delicious one ;-)
Happy New Year. 🥂 to better 2023

My Acacia is in full bloom and the house is hidden behind a glorious golden cloud. 
It smells heavenly 💛
I am so proud of my sister @karolina_maszkiewicz Her beautiful sculptures right now on display in @twentieth.gallery
Misty mornings, gentle days and evenings by the fire. Spend few days in the cabin and this was our view ;-)
Here’s to strong women all around the world. May we know them. May we be them. May we support them.
Bit of gloomy Sunday over here. I hope you have a good one.
I have never been a big fan of yellow and orange colors but lately I have been going on daily sunset walks and maybe I am developing a new appreciation for them ;-)

Rainy winter gave us a beautiful spring full of wildflowers. California poppy season is in full bloom. I grow the cream version in my garden but the wild ones are fiery orange. We took a quick trip outside the city to take in the view🧡
Embracing the beauty of imperfections. Even when we fall apart we can find strength in vulnerability. That’s what I am telling myself today ;-)

Celebrating the beauty of my little corner of paradise.
Whether I am picking fresh flowers, sipping a cup of tea or simply basking in the golden sunlight, my meadow garden fills my heart with gratitude and awe.

Hey LA friends! My sister is part of a group exhibit called "Temporal" at @tappancollective and I would love for you to join me in supporting her at the art opening on June 22. Come check out some amazing art and show some love for my talented sis!

Everything's Blooming in the Garden!
There's something magical about cultivating these flowers from tiny seeds, nurturing them with love and care, and witnessing them flourish into these lovely blossoms. 
Homegrown Happiness💐

Hello from the road. As we head up the coast it’s hard not to get swept away by the magic of California coast! But it's not just the breathtaking scenery that's making this road trip so special. Somehow, I seem to find flowers everywhere I go:-)
The blushing sunrises, crashing waves, stunning coastal drives, towering redwoods California truly has it all! We just keep on driving:-)

Traveling bouquet. On this unforgettable adventure, I've decided to create a one-of-a-kind bouquet using the beautiful wild flowers I find along the roadside. As the miles go by, some flowers may gently fade, but that only makes room for fresh blooms to join the journey, adding their charm and fragrance to this ever-evolving bouquet :-)

Dahlia season is finally here! Unfortunately, this year's harvest hasn't been as abundant as I had hoped. But you know what? I'm cherishing every single bloom even more because of it! Rest of the garden is doing ok and despite my unintentional neglect and scorching heat that LA is experiencing lately. The garden stairs have taken on a charmingly wild quality and navigating them has turned into a bit of a fun challenge!

Back from an unforgettable Yosemite weekend, and it was a true adventure! Our campsite at Cathedral Lakes meant carrying my hefty 20 lbs backpack through it all. Rain, hail, and chilly temperatures tried, but they couldn't dampen Yosemite's allure. 🏞️❄️⛺
The end-of-summer vibes are in the air, even here in always-sunny LA. My roses are starting to perk up, and I’m hopeful for the reappearance of my reblooming irises. The last of the pool weather?

Dose of autumn colors. We went  chasing fall in Inyo National Forest 🌲🍁

From Lake Sabrina to Gorge Lake, it was a challenging trek, with unexpected weather twists – rain, snow, and a freezing tent night! But it was all worth it.

Took a while to recover, but memories like these are priceless

Autumn vibes, but the beach weather's back! 🍂🏖️ #EndlessSummer 
#AutumnColors #FallingForFall #AutumnMagic #FallVibes #AutumnDays
